<paragraph id="E121FE277774FFBF19F14FA2FE1CEB95" blockId="12.[351,556,1173,1229]" box="[405,502,1205,1229]" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">
<figureCitation id="79A5E2A27774FFBF19F14FA2FE1CEB95" box="[405,502,1205,1229]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[151,186,1275,1297]" captionTargetBox="[159,1432,267,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-205@9.[151,1438,257,1198]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 6: Rhynchonelliden. a: Fortunella? acutiloba (Eud.-Desl.), Liesberg Amtil, spätes Callovien, Athleta-Zone (FPJ 5038); b: Laevigaterhynchia triplicosa (Wisniew.-Zelichow.), Col de la Croix, spätes Callovien, Athleta-Zone (FPJ 5039); c: Laevigaterhynchia cf. triplicosa (Wisniew.-Zelichow.), Col de la Croix, frühes Callovien, Herveyi-Zone? (FPJ 5040); d: Ivanoviella oxoniensis (Rollier), frühes Callovien, Herveyi-Zone? (FPJ 5041); e: Kallirhynchia? sp.1, Tunnel du Graitery, frühes Callovien, Herveyi-Zone (FPJ 5042); f: Kallirhynchia? sp.2, Tunnel du Graitery, frühes Callovien, Herveyi-Zone (FPJ 5043); g: Septaliphoria orbignyana (Oppel), Craitery (Combe d’Eschert), mittleres Callovien, Coronatum-Zone (FPJ 5044); h: Robustirhynchia ehningensis (Quenst.), Liesberg Amtil, frühes Callovien, Calloviense-Zone (FPJ 5045). Massstäbe: 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6448489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6448489/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">Fig. 6e, f</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A984ADAC7774FFBF18F34FE3FF05E83D" pageId="12" pageNumber="49" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="E121FE277774FFBF18F34FE3FEC3EA14" blockId="12.[151,756,1268,1356]" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357774FFBF18F34FE3FEEEEA54" bold="true" box="[151,260,1268,1292]" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">Material:</emphasis>
<specimenCount id="F79835AE7774FFBF19704FE2FEB2EA54" box="[276,344,1269,1293]" pageId="12" pageNumber="49" type="generic">1 Ex.</specimenCount>
, Tunnel du Raimeux, 
<specimenCount id="F79835AE7774FFBF1A0D4FE2FD47EA54" box="[617,685,1269,1293]" pageId="12" pageNumber="49" type="generic">2 Ex.</specimenCount>
, Tun- nel du Graitery, Frühes Callovien, Herveyi- bis frühe Königi-Zone.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E121FE277774FFBF18F34E64FEF3E9BE" blockId="12.[151,756,1395,1766]" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357774FFBF18F34E64FEAAEAD3" bold="true" box="[151,320,1395,1419]" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">Bemerkungen:</emphasis>
Die vorliegenden Einzelstücke (
<figureCitation id="79A5E2A27774FFBF1AC54E64FF49EAF2" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[151,186,1275,1297]" captionTargetBox="[159,1432,267,1197]" captionTargetId="figure-205@9.[151,1438,257,1198]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 6: Rhynchonelliden. a: Fortunella? acutiloba (Eud.-Desl.), Liesberg Amtil, spätes Callovien, Athleta-Zone (FPJ 5038); b: Laevigaterhynchia triplicosa (Wisniew.-Zelichow.), Col de la Croix, spätes Callovien, Athleta-Zone (FPJ 5039); c: Laevigaterhynchia cf. triplicosa (Wisniew.-Zelichow.), Col de la Croix, frühes Callovien, Herveyi-Zone? (FPJ 5040); d: Ivanoviella oxoniensis (Rollier), frühes Callovien, Herveyi-Zone? (FPJ 5041); e: Kallirhynchia? sp.1, Tunnel du Graitery, frühes Callovien, Herveyi-Zone (FPJ 5042); f: Kallirhynchia? sp.2, Tunnel du Graitery, frühes Callovien, Herveyi-Zone (FPJ 5043); g: Septaliphoria orbignyana (Oppel), Craitery (Combe d’Eschert), mittleres Callovien, Coronatum-Zone (FPJ 5044); h: Robustirhynchia ehningensis (Quenst.), Liesberg Amtil, frühes Callovien, Calloviense-Zone (FPJ 5045). Massstäbe: 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6448489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6448489/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">Fig. 6e, f</figureCitation>
), die provisorisch der Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47774FFBF19924E85FD60EAF2" authorityName="Buckman" authorityYear="1918" box="[502,650,1426,1450]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Wellerellidae" genus="Kallirhynchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="12" pageNumber="49" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357774FFBF19924E85FD60EAF2" box="[502,650,1426,1450]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">Kallirhynchia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
zugewiesen werden, gleichen äusserlich 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47774FFBF198D4EA4FD1EEA92" authority="(J. Sowerby)" baseAuthorityName="J. Sowerby" box="[489,756,1458,1482]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="12" pageNumber="49" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="concinna">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357774FFBF198D4EA4FD82EA92" box="[489,616,1459,1482]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">K. concinna</emphasis>
(J. Sowerby)
</taxonomicName>
und 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47774FFBF18A24EC5FE17EAB2" authority="Buckman, 1918" authorityName="Buckman" authorityYear="1918" box="[198,509,1490,1514]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Wellerellidae" genus="Kallirhynchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="12" pageNumber="49" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="indentata">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357774FFBF18A24EC5FEA0EAB2" box="[198,330,1490,1514]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">K. indentata</emphasis>
Buckman, 1918
</taxonomicName>
. Daneben stellte Buckman eine ganze Serie neuer Taxa (
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47774FFBF1A624EE5FD7AE951" authorityName="Buckman" authorityYear="1917" box="[518,656,1522,1545]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Wellerellidae" genus="Kallirhynchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="12" pageNumber="49" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="constricta">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357774FFBF1A624EE5FD7AE951" box="[518,656,1522,1545]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">K. constricta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="D3EA22357774FFBF1AF94EE6FDCFE971" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">anglica, expansa, superba, orbis, lauta, bella</emphasis>
) auf, die z. 
<collectionCode id="878F66E27774FFBF1AC64D06FD5FE970" box="[674,693,1553,1576]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">T</collectionCode>
. auch von Muir-Wood (1936) übernommen wurden, aber wahrscheinlich nur Varianten von 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47774FFBF1A634D46FD66E930" authorityName="Buckman" authorityYear="1918" box="[519,652,1616,1640]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Wellerellidae" genus="Kallirhynchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="12" pageNumber="49" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="indentata">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357774FFBF1A634D46FD66E930" box="[519,652,1616,1640]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">K. indentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sind. Die Unterschiede betreffen die Form des Schalenumrisses, die Gestalt des Profils, die Feinheit der Berippung und der gezähnten Kommissur, besonders deutlich am vorderen Rand.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E121FE277774FFBF18934C19FF05E83D" blockId="12.[151,756,1806,1893]" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">
Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="269E85A47774FFBF19304C19FEE8E81D" authority="Seifert, 1963 Typusart" authorityName="Seifert" authorityYear="1963" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Tetrarhynchiidae" genus="Robustirhynchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="12" pageNumber="49" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D3EA22357774FFBF19304C19FDEEE87E" box="[340,516,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">Robustirhynchia</emphasis>
Seifert, 1963 
<emphasis id="D3EA22357774FFBF18F34C3AFEE8E81D" bold="true" box="[151,258,1837,1861]" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">Typusart</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="D3EA22357774FFBF19674C3AFEE2E81D" bold="true" box="[259,264,1837,1861]" pageId="12" pageNumber="49">:</emphasis>
